text:
There's a bug in the latest ant-junit version 1.9.6. In the JUnitTestRunner#run method
there is tried to load the class CustomJUnit4TestAdapterCache but it does not exist. I
think it has been removed in a previous version and someone forgot to update the run
method accordingly.

Here's the relevant line from the JUnitTestRunner#run method:

--java

try{

  junit4TestAdapterCacheClass = Class.forName(
    "org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit.CustomJUnit4TestAdapterCache");

} catch (final ClassNotFoundException e) {
  // OK, fall back to JUnit 3.
}

--

The implication is that every test is executed by the junit 3 runner. This lead to
ant telling me: no tests found.
